he would take a nap under it. He told people that the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, had done so. Source: Musnad al-Bazza\u0304r 1519 Grade: Hasan (fair) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34610,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/11\/30\/ibn-umar-humility-outcasts\/","url_meta":{"origin":43965,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Umar on Humility: Ibn Umar eats with lepers and outcasts","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 30, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Bakr ibn Hafs reported: Ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, while travelling between Mecca and Medina would not withhold his food from a leper, nor an outcast, nor anyone afflicted, even letting them sit with him at his table. Source: al-Zuhd wal-Raqa\u0304\u2019iq 611 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0628\u064e\u0643\u0652\u0631\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25413,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/13\/shorten-prayers-travel\/","url_meta":{"origin":43965,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Permission to shorten prayers during travel","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 13, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: We went out with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, from Medina to Mecca and he would pray two cycles\u00a0at a time until he re